decks.notes: The deck focuses on establishing control over the board through removal spells and counterspells while continuously drawing cards to maintain card advantage. It aims to stall the game with board wipes like Day of Judgment and tempo plays like Temporary Lockdown, eventually overwhelming the opponent with powerful late-game threats like Jace, the Perfected Mind and Overlord of the Mistmoors. The deck also includes ways to gain life and protect itself, ensuring it can survive long enough to execute its game plan and outvalue the opponent in the late game.

The main concept of this Jeskai Aggro deck is to swarm the board with aggressive creatures quickly while controlling the opponent's board with removal spells and disruptive creatures. The deck focuses on utilizing low-cost creatures like Novice Inspector and Spyglass Siren to apply pressure early on, with the ability to buff them with cards like Resolute Reinforcements. The deck also includes a mix of lands to ensure consistency in mana production. Ultimately, the goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and aggressive strategy while maintaining some control over the game.

This Rakdos Aggro deck focuses on overwhelming the opponent with a combination of aggressive creatures and powerful combat tricks. By utilizing cards like Monstrous Rage and Might of the Meek to pump up your creatures, paired with Leyline of Resonance to control the opponent's resources, this deck aims to quickly deplete the opponent's life total before they have a chance to stabilize. The deck also includes creature cards like Emberheart Challenger and Heartfire Hero to provide additional damage and pressure on the opponent. With proper timing and sequencing of plays, this deck can quickly overwhelm opponents and secure victories.
